---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const updated = 'March 2026';

const privacySchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  '@id': 'https://tobyonfitnesstech.com/privacy#webpage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy | Toby on Fitness Tech',
  description:
    'Privacy Policy for Toby on Fitness Tech, including wearable data sources, automation workflows, and how data is used and stored.',
  url: 'https://tobyonfitnesstech.com/privacy',
  inLanguage: 'en',
  isPartOf: {
    '@id': 'https://tobyonfitnesstech.com/#website',
  },
  about: {
    '@id': 'https://tobyonfitnesstech.com/#organization',
  },
  author: {
    '@id': 'https://tobyonfitnesstech.com/#toby',
  },
};
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Toby on Fitness Tech"
  description="Read how TobyOnFitnessTech handles data from WHOOP, Garmin, 8Sleep, Speediance, and OpenClaw workflows for fitness tracking and AI-powered reporting."
  jsonLd={privacySchema}
>
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 text-white border-b border-neutral-800">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-400 max-w-3xl">
        TobyOnFitnessTech documents real-world fitness training, wearable data, and automation workflows.
        This policy explains what data is used, how it is processed, and how it is protected.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-neutral-950 text-neutral-200">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 md:py-16 space-y-10 leading-relaxed">
      <section class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          TobyOnFitnessTech is a personal website operated by Toby Glenn Peters. The site focuses on
          fitness technology, including wearable metrics, training logs, and automated summaries powered
          by OpenClaw. We collect and process only the data needed to run the site, generate personal
          performance insights, and publish educational fitness content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">Data may include the following categories from connected tools and services:</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 list-disc pl-6 marker:text-blue-400">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-white">WHOOP:</span> recovery scores, strain, sleep metrics,
            resting heart rate, and heart-rate variability trends.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-white">Garmin:</span> activities, distance, pace, heart rate,
            training load, and workout summaries.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-white">8Sleep:</span> sleep duration, sleep staging,
            temperature-related sleep insights, and overnight recovery context.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-white">Speediance:</span> workout sessions, exercise logs,
            reps, sets, resistance, and volume totals.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-white">OpenClaw automation:</span> metadata used to generate
            morning and nightly fitness reports, workflow timestamps, and summarized performance outputs.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">3. How Data Is Used</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">Collected data is used for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 list-disc pl-6 marker:text-blue-400">
          <li>Personal fitness tracking and longitudinal trend analysis.</li>
          <li>AI-powered performance reports and training summaries.</li>
          <li>Morning readiness and nightly recap reports generated through automation workflows.</li>
          <li>Educational content and product analysis shared on TobyOnFitnessTech.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">4. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Data may be stored in local systems (including personal logs and project files) and in selected
          cloud services used for sync, backup, and automation execution. We retain data only as long as
          needed for ongoing tracking, reporting, and site operations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">5. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          TobyOnFitnessTech uses minimal cookies. We do not use invasive ad-tech tracking. Any analytics
          are lightweight and intended only to understand overall site performance and readership trends.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/40 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">6. Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          For privacy-related questions, corrections, or requests, email
          <a href="mailto:toby@tobyonfitness.tech" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline-offset-4 hover:underline">toby@tobyonfitness.tech</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
